# Micro:bit Setup

<div style="background-color: #a6e3e8; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px; margin-bottom:10px;">

<p style="line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; ">These steps are designed for Google Chrome and Microsoft Edge web browsers released in March 2021 or later. If you are using a Chromebook, you will need to be on V90 or above.
</p></div>

### Expand one step at a time as you work through the steps to help you stay organized.

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🔌 Step 1 - Plug in device.</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom:150px;">
 <p><img src="https://images.code.org/211f377fb4e4c1addb2cc33d53bca6f6-Micro_bit Overview.png" style="width: 300px; float:left; margin: -10px 10px -10px -30px;">

#### The <strong>USB connector</strong> allows you to plug the micro:bit in. Plugging it in lets you communicate with the board in App Lab, but it also provides electricity to the board so that it can do things like turn on the LED Display.



</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">📋 Step 2 - Open Maker Setup Page </summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p>

##### Visit <a href="https://studio.code.org/maker/setup" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">maker setup page</a>.
##### Have this page open for any quick reference needed.

</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">▶️ Step 3 - Connect to Board.</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom:30px;">
    <p><img src="https://images.code.org/3daea92e305f47f2078af2aa20f7dc1c-image-1681158674980.png" style="width:200px; margin:-10px 25px 1px 10px; float:left;">

#### Click the <strong>Connect To Board</strong> button.
</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">❕ Step 4 - Serial Port Pop-up</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 160px;">
    <p><img src="https://images.code.org/8015fe82160749c571050f6e6d158896-image-1681161196976.png" style="width:300px; margin: 5px 20px 0px 10px; float:left;">

#### A window will pop up - something similar to a micro:bit device will appear in this window such as 'BBC micro:bit CMSIS-DAP' or 'mbed Serial Port'. Select it, then press the **Connect** button. 


##### **If this window doesn't pop up or if the screen is blank:** See our <a href="https://support.code.org/hc/en-us/articles/9953258694669" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Troubleshooting WebSerial Support Article</a>

</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">❗ Step 5 - Expected Fail Message!</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom:20px;">
    <p><img src="https://images.code.org/4c4dd175dd548ef9fc95741cf17df2e8-image-1681159311256.png" style="width:500px; margin:5px 20px 0px 10px; float:left;">

#### This process will **fail on the Board Connectable step** (this is expected!) - press the **Update micro:bit** button.

##### **If you continue to see a red X after pressing this button:** <a href="https://support.code.org/hc/en-us/articles/13937009908877-Installing-BBC-micro-bit-software-for-Code-org#h_01GVCCV0VX7G7HNYMYFSSSFK9N" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Skip to the alternative installation method.</a>

</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">❕ Step 6 - Second Pop-up Window</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p>

#### A second window will pop-up, listing a micro:bit device (the name may be different from the first window). Select the  micro:bit device, then click **Connect**.


##### If this window doesn't pop up or is blank: <a href="https://support.code.org/hc/en-us/articles/13937009908877-Installing-BBC-micro-bit-software-for-Code-org#h_01GVCCV0VX7G7HNYMYFSSSFK9N" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Skip to the alternative installation method.</a>

</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">💬 Step 7 - Installing Software Message</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p><img src="https://images.code.org/9ac72c433f0b1940fd86352308123913-image-1681159721549.png" style="width:450px; margin: 5px 20px 1px 10px; float:left;">

#### The step will update to show it is installing the micro:bit software. You will see the progress update automatically.

</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🔁 Step 8 - Re-Detect</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom:100px;">
    <p><img src="https://images.code.org/187f771da2216216c634cac3885463f5-image-1681159788553.png" style="width:400px; float:left; margin: 2px 20px 0px 5px;">

#### When it is finished, press the *re-detect* button at the top of these steps.

</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">▶️ Step 9 - Connect to Board - Again</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p><img src="https://images.code.org/3daea92e305f47f2078af2aa20f7dc1c-image-1681158674980.png" style="width:200px; margin:-10px 25px 1px 10px; float:left;">

#### When the page reloads, click **Connect to Board** again, and re-select the micro:bit device from the pop-up window
</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">💪🏼 Step 10 - Connected!</summary>
 <div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom:60px;">
    <p><img src="https://images.code.org/d57d2f3aafb07241e39dfb90e0b4162e-image-1681159872902.png" style="width:300px; margin: 1px 20px 1px 10px; float:left;">

#### The board should connect. You can tell because the website will update, and the micro:bit itself will show a checkmark animation before disappearing.
</p></div>
</details>

<div style="clear:both"/>

![]()
